Custer Schoolhouse • built around 1884, between 7th and 8th Streets on Montgomery Street.

Hermosa School
August 31 at 7:27 AM ·

Dear Parent/Guardian

We have a backpack program available at Hermosa School. The program is designed to provide non-perishable food every Thursday to children that would benefit from supplemental nourishment over the weekend. Bags will be dispensed in a discreet and caring manner. There is no cost associated to this program. If you wish for your child to participate in the program please call or email Sonja Tennyson at Sonja.tennyson@k12.sd.us or (605) 255—4345 and let her know you want your child to participate in the Blessings in a Backpack program. Please include your child’s name and grade level.

August 22 at 11:21 AM ·

School 🏫 starts this Wednesday. We cannot have students in our building until 7:30 am. ⏰
Mon. & Wed. 1st, 4th & 5th report directly to their classroom.
Tues. & Thurs. JK, K 2nd and 3rd report to their classroom.
They will alternate being out on respective playgrounds opposite days.
6th goes directly to our gym Mon.-Thur.

**Parents/Guardians will remain outside our building, dropping off or picking up students after school.
We thank you in advance for your support and understanding!💜🐾💜🐾

Custer Jr/Sr High School
June 24 at 8:17 PM ·

Families and Friends of Custer School District

A quick update about graduation, this Saturday, June 27th at 2:00 pm.

The city voted to re-open Custer and with that means we can open graduation to the public.

Location One: Football Field
No tickets will be required.
Families and Friends need to bring their own seating for the grass field. The graduates will be seated in the stands.
Please respect the desires of people that would like to social distance.

Location Two: Armory (Only if weather prohibits an outdoor ceremony and if so, an all call will be made at 7:00 am)
Gold tickets (Mailed to graduate Primary Households) are required for seating on the main floor. Everyone else will be seated in the stands.

Please respect the desire of people that want to social distance.

We are excited to be celebrating the Class of 2020, please make them the focus and join us in our celebration.

(P.S. Graduates need to arrive by 1:00 pm.)

post_text:
Recognizing two CSD retirees this year:
**Karen Hammer for 42 Years of Teaching. Karen was a teacher at Hermosa School, Spring Creek School & Custer Elementary over her four decades plus! Karen is pictured with Hermosa Principal Lori Enright. Karen will have a plaque on the back of the CHS Theatre Seat commemorating her years of service.

**Jan Wilson for 27 years of service. Jan started out as a substitute, then a para, and eventually as an Administrative Assistant in all of the school buildings in Custer over her years. Jan is pictured with Supt. Mark Naugle receiving her retirement plaque.

These ladies have positively touched the lives of thousands of students and their families as well as hundreds of CSD staff. Thank you for your dedication and friendship.
Karen & Jan ~ "you will be missed" is an understatement! All the best to you both! Enjoy your retirement years.

Custer School District meal deliveries have been extended throughout the summer. The meal delivery days and times have had to be adjusted.

Tuesdays and Thursdays: CES – Door C pick-up will go from 11:00am-11:20am. The Pringle (11:15am) and 4-Mile (12:00pm) deliveries will remain the same. The intersection of Highway 385 & Highway 16 delivery will be from 11:45am-12:00pm. Aspen View will be from 12:10pm-12:30pm. Triple T will be from 12:45pm-1:00pm. There will no longer be an armory delivery. Those wanting meals will need to come to the drop-off points at the new times. Students will still get breakfasts and lunches for 7 days a week but within the two deliveries instead of the three deliveries, we had been doing each week. Thank you. Have a great summer!

text:
Please join us to celebrate the Custer High School class of 2020 with a stationary parade on Saturday, May 16 from 2 pm to 3 pm. The students will be lined up on the southside of Washington St and the street will be open for one-way traffic (East to West from 8th St. to 2nd St.) for spectators to drive through and view. Please remember to maintain social distancing when viewing the graduates.

*** Please remember that Washington will be One-Way (East to West from 8th St. to 2nd St.) on Saturday from 1pm-4pm to accommodate this parade***

Stay tuned for more info. However, this parade event is in place of what would have been graduation day for our seniors. Let's show these seniors we are still thinking of them and supporting them through these unusual times!! Go Cats! #Custercommunitystrong

May 5 at 8:53 AM · Custer, SD ·

More than 1,000 pounds of ground beef were donated to Custer School District 16-1 this school year by local ranchers -- how cool is that?! Many thanks to the Custer County Chronicle for following up on the new beef donation partnership with the district, and thanks to all the ranchers who have participated. We're happy to help support this partnership by incorporating the donated beef into our school menus! #farmtoschool #schoollunch

post_text: To all our Jr/Sr High Students & Families ~ Monday, April 6, from 6:30 am – 2:00 pm. - Homework Drop-Off / Pick-up - we will have you pull up in your vehicle in front of the school and a staff member will give your packet to you in the vehicle. All students are required to participate in this distance education. This is not optional. If you know of someone in need of assistance, please let us know and we can reach out to them. Thank you for all you are doing to help us educate our students! If you have any questions or concerns, please contact Principal Orion Thompson or Admin. Assistant Jan Wilson at 673-4473.

post_text: For our Hermosa Students & their Families ~ this is now moved to April ￼6 due to forecasted storm.
shared_text:
Hermosa School
March 26 at 11:44 AM ·

Hello Hermosa Families, Starting April 2nd, we will have weekly homework pick-up and drop off every Thursday from 6:30am to 2pm. All Junior Kindergarten through 5th grade teachers will have the items ready for pick-up and will be expecting homework turned in. The middle school is all online so they will not have the pick-up. Most of our families are working hard with the teachers to educate our students and having wonderful experiences. Unfortunately, we have some that are not participating. We absolutely need every student to participate in the distance learning. If students do not participate, they will be required to do summer school and possibly even be retained. If you know of someone in need of assistance, please let me know and we can reach out to them. Thank you for all you are doing to help us educate our students!

NOTICE OF VACANCY ON SCHOOL BOARD
CUSTER SCHOOL DISTRICT 16-1

Three positions on the Custer School District Board of Education will become vacant due to the expiration of the present terms of office of the following school board members:

Bob Morgan, Jr’s chair - Three (3) year term
Travis Hartshorn’s chair - Three (3) year term
Jared Carson’s chair - Three (3) year term

Circulation of nominating petitions may begin on Sunday, March 1, 2020. Petitions may be filed in the office of the business manager located at 527 Montgomery Street, Custer, SD, between the hours of 7:30 a.m. and 4:30 p.m. Monday through Thursday, and 8:00 a.m. and 1:00 p.m. on Fridays. Petitions must be filed no later than Tuesday, March 31, 2020, at 5:00 p.m., or mailed by registered mail not later than March 31, 2020, at 5:00 p.m.

post_text: We appreciate our Teammates Mentors!
shared_text:
Custer Elementary School
February 5 at 1:52 PM ·

Another one of our awesome TEAMMATES mentors! Please consider joining our team!♥️ A young man came to me today and asked how can he have a Mentor? He stated he sees other kids with them and would like to have one. Broke my heart to say we have 5 other boys that have been waiting over a year for their mentor. YOU are needed!

post_text:
Custer Kindergarten/Jr Kindergarten Roundup/Screening Date Change

Custer Elementary Kindergarten "Roundup" Screening & Pre-registration will be March 25th and 26th for children entering kindergarten in August 2020. Please help spread the word to families who have children old enough for kindergarten to let them know it will be earlier this year. Watch for more information in March. There will be no Kindergarten /Jr. Kindergarten those two days.
